comments.body:
There are two cases here;

 1. mta2mta or `smtp` service; this could be constrained to one or a few public keys or certificates;
 2. cli2mta, or `submission` service; this could be supported with a Root/Intermediate CA to avoid showing users in DNS and to avoid being dependent on DNS update times after userbase changes

The idea I proposed, of desktop/phone users as DANE Clients applies to 2. but I don't know about 1.
